com.hcl.domino.data

Enum Find

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Find>
      • com.hcl.domino.data.Find
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Find>

    public enum Find
extends Enum<Find>
    These flags are used by DominoCollection.getAllIdsByKey(Set, Object) to control how the collection is searched for the key. The flags, PARTIAL, CASE_INSENSITIVE, and ACCENT_INSENSITIVE should only be used for character data, since a "partial number" or "partial date" is not well defined.

    The LESS_THAN and GREATER_THAN flags refer to the way the sorted column keys are ordered and displayed, not the way they compare with each other. LESS_THAN means "find the entry before" and GREATER_THAN means "find the entry after" a desired key. The LESS_THAN and GREATER_THAN flags will result in success if at least one key that is less than or greater than the specified key, respectively, is found.

    If a FIRST_EQUAL or LAST_EQUAL comparison is specified and the number of matches is requested to be returned, then the number of entries which match the specified key will be returned. If a LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN comparison is specified, then the number of matching entries cannot be requested.

      GREATER_THAN
      Find first entry greater than the key value.
      LAST_EQUAL

      Find last entry less than the key value.

      MATCH_CATEGORYANDLEAF

      MATCH_CATEGORYORLEAF

      Return only entries which hNames would disallow (requires full access set)
      PARTIAL

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • PARTIAL

        public static final Find PARTIAL
        Match only the initial characters ("T" matches "Tim", "i" does not match "Tim"). If multiple keys are used, a partial match is done on each of the keys in the order that they are specified. A partial match must be found for all specified keys in order for a particular entry to be considered a successful match.
